criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Elderly men with age ranging from 60 to 80 years in condition to participate in the
             strength training program.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Individuals who already participate in strength training programs;

          -  Individuals who participated in strength training programs less than three months
             before the beginning of the study;

          -  Individuals with any kind musculoskeletal injuries in the lower limbs that impair the
             performance of the exercises;

          -  Individuals with contraindications to the performance of high intensity exercises,
             such as cardiovascular or neurological diseases;

          -  Individuals with difficulties in understanding and/or performing the exercises;

          -  Individuals who did not attend to at least 85% of the sessions or had 02 consecutive
             absences and did not recover them.
